# Catching 404s

In Express, any route that doesn't match will fall through. To handle 404, add a middleware at the **end** of all routes that sends a 404 response.

```javascript
// After all your routes
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.status(404).send('Sorry, page not found');
});
```

This middleware only runs if no route handled the request.

## Custom Error Handlers

Error-handling middleware takes **four** parameters: `(err, req, res, next)`.

```javascript
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(500).send('Something broke!');
});
```

Place this after all routes and other middleware. When you call `next(err)` in a route, Express jumps to error-handling middleware.

slides.codeSnippet:
app.get('/broken', (req, res, next) => {
  const err = new Error('Something went wrong');
  next(err); // pass to error handler
});

// Error handler
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  res.status(500).json({ error: err.message });
});
